     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Oracle[f, {c1, c2, ..., cm}, {t1, t2, ..., tn}] represents the quantum \
oracle corresponding to the classical oracle f : {0, 1} m -> {0, 1} n, using \
the ancillary qubits {t1, t2, ..., tn} controlled by the native qubits {c1, \
c2, ..., cm}. Oracle[f, m, n] represents the classical oracle f : {0, 1} m -> \
{0, 1} n that provides the flexibility of the input form while keeping the \
consistency of the output form.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
